bug.short_desc: Generator replaces both identifier of method and strings found in method body

long_desc.thetext: According to Thomas, this is expected behavior for private members.

I'm closing this as duplicate of bug#1927. The arguments from back then still hold: We need string references to members, including private members, for property definitions and destruct functions. While the string parameter passed to methods like this._disposeObjects could possibly be made into code references, the string values in property settings are needed, as the generated getter and setter for properties are constructed from strings. This could only be abolished if the whole property system is rewritten to not construct functions from strings.
To better document these issues for the privates optimization I have created dedicated manual page, documentation/manual/source/pages/tool/generator_optimizations.rst, to contain this.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 1927 ***
